  "title": "👨‍🍳 Central Kitchen Assistant (Food Production) | Geylang | Up to $2,700 + VB",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>Join a production team that prepares healthy and balanced ingredients for multiple café outlets islandwide. Training will be provided for motivated individuals who enjoy hands-on kitchen work.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in food preparation (cutting, portioning, packing ingredients)</li><li>Maintain kitchen cleanliness and hygiene standards</li><li>Operate kitchen equipment safely</li><li>Load and unload supplies and ingredients</li><li>Follow food safety and NEA compliance procedures</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible, punctual, and a good team player</li><li>Physically fit and comfortable with kitchen duties</li><li>No experience required — training provided</li></ul><p><strong>Work Details</strong></p><ul><li>Working Hours: 44 hours/week</li><li>Rest Day: 1 day per week (roster-based)</li><li>Benefits: Uniforms, staff discounts, annual leave starting from 7 days</li><li>Bonus: Performance-based</li></ul><p>EA License No: 23C1703 </p><p>EA Personnel No: R1762582 </p><p>EA Personnel Name: Wong Choo Sian, Jabez</p>",
